<div class="container my-5">
  <div class="text-center mb-4">
    <h2 class="section-title">My Service Learning Experiences</h2>
    <p>View my CCA Transcript here (will put later)</p>
  </div>

  <div class="row gy-4 justify-content-center">

    <!-- Session 1 -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/youtube.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="YouTube Workshop for Seniors">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 1</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">YouTube Workshop for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Volunteer</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Guided seniors in basic YouTube navigation</li>
            <li>Demonstrated volume control and playback</li>
            <li>Explained step-by-step usage</li>
            <li>Communicated in Malay to assist Malay-speaking seniors</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            From this experience, I realised that explaining technical concepts in simple terms is crucial when teaching seniors.<br><br>
            I learned to be patient and empathetic, understanding that everyone learns at their own pace and to adapt my teaching approach to suit the needs of each participant.<br><br>
            This session also improved my communication skills, and ability to engage learners with different backgrounds.<br><br>
            This experience made me more aware of the challenges seniors face when using technology and motivated me to continue volunteering and making a positive impact in my community.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Teamwork</li>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Teaching</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Session 2 -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/piccollage1.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="PicCollage Workshop">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 2</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">PicCollage Workshop for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Volunteer</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Guided seniors to create digital memories with PicCollage</li>
            <li>Reviewed templates, stickers, text and filters</li>
            <li>Provided one-on-one support for seniors</li>
            <li>Communicated in Malay</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            Guiding seniors through the PicCollage workshop showed me that digital creativity can be enjoyed by anyone, regardless of age or technical experience.<br><br>
            I learned to balance giving instructions with allowing seniors the freedom to explore independently, which not only strengthened my teaching skills but also helped build their confidence.<br><br>
            This session also highlighted the importance of clear and culturally sensitive communication, and using Malay to connect effectively with the seniors improved my ability to engage diverse learners.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Patience</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Session 3 -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/chatgpt_workshop.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="ChatGPT Workshop">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 3</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Introduction to ChatGPT for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Participant</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Introduced seniors to ChatGPT basics and practical uses</li>
            <li>Demonstrated tasks like recipes (Nasi Minyak) and learning aid examples</li>
            <li>Explained AI in simple terms and used Malay for clarity</li>
            <li>Presented in English to improve public speaking</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            Volunteering to teach seniors how to use ChatGPT was a meaningful experience that highlighted the importance of making technology like AI, accessible to all<br><br>
            Guiding them through basic tasks of ChatGPT, such as generating recipes helped me appreciate how AI can be used to support daily tasks and learning.<br><br>
            This session also enhanced my public speaking skills, as I took the initiative to present in English to a group of seniors, which was a valuable opportunity to practice clear and effective communication.<br><br>
            Overall, this service learning session strengthened my teaching abilities, public speaking skills and empathy. It has also motivated me to continue to give back to the community by helping seniors learn how to use, explore and benefit from new technologies.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Teaching</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Session 4 -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/capcutservicelearning.png" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="Capcut Service Learning">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 4</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Capcut Workshop at Greenwood Primary School</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Student Volunteer Teacher</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Assigned to a group of Primary Four students to guide them during their enrichment programme using capcut</li>
            <li>Taught basic video editing skills such as trimming, velocity, transitions and effects.</li>
            <li>Explained concepts in simple, step-by-step instructions for better understanding</li>
            <li>Adapted explanations to suit students with different attention spans.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            This experience helped me develop patience and improve my ability to to explain technical concepts in a clear and simple manner.<br><br>
            Working with students of different attention spans required me to adapt my communication style and approach, to suit students of different learning levels.<br><br>
            It was meaningful to contribute to the community by helping younger students gain exposure to digital tools and basic video editing skills.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Teamwork</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Session 5 (FIXED POSITION ONLY) -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/ygos5.png" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="YGOS Workshop Session 5">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">YGOS Workshop Session 5</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">YGOS Treasure Hunt Activity</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Station Master - UNO Stress Station</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Facilitated the UNO stress station during the YGOS treasure hunt activity</li>
            <li>Explained game rules clearly, step-by-step to youth participants before gameplay as most were unfamiliar with the game</li>
            <li>Guided participants throughout the activity to ensure smooth participation.</li>
            <li>Encouraged engagement and ensured inclusivity for all participants.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            This was another experience that helped me develop patience and adaptability when working with youths of different learning styles. <br><br>
            As not all participants were familiar with the game, I learned to adjust my explanations and approach to ensure everyone could participate comfortably.<br><br>
            I learned to adjust my explanations and approach to ensure everyone understood the roles and could participate comfortably<br><br>
            It also improved my confidence in managing small group activities and engaging actively with youths.
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Patience & Adaptability</li>
            <li>Confidence in Leading Activities</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
